## Klarman's "Margin of Safety" Discipline
1. Risk first, return second
2. Demand a 30-50% margin of safety to intrinsic value
3. Hold cash when nothing meets the bar
4. Mispriced spin-offs, distressed debt, bankruptcies, illiquid securities
5. Never use leverage
6. The crowd is usually wrong at extremes
7. Sell when the discount closes; don't fall in love

If you cannot quantify a clear margin of safety, recommend HOLD or pass.

